        <h3>ISS Web Publishing</h3>
        <p>
          Welcome to the <a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/iss/" title="Information Systems and 
Services">ISS</a> Web Publishing Service for members of the <a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk">Newcastle 
University</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page (the file <em>iss_example.html</em>) is created by default when your web publishing account is set up. Now that you can read this,
          your account is ready for use. You can use this page as a starting point for developing
          your own site, or you can upload something completely new. We recommend you keep a copy of this page for
          your reference.
        </p>
        <p>
          The useful resources section points you to some information which you may find helpful when developing your site.
          This is a small subset of the resources which are available - you can find further resources by using the <a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/search/">University 
          Search Engine</a>, or by using <a href="http://www.google.com">Google</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          For beginners, you might like to start by viewing the source code of this page (commonly via the View -&gt; Source menu option in your browser).
          That should show you how a basic <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr> page is set up, along with a little bit
          of <a href="http://www.htmlhelp.com/reference/css/quick-tutorial.html" title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</a> to make it look nice.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are looking for something more than basic HTML, the <a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/web-development/guides/php/">PHP Scripting Language</a> is 
          installed on this server. If you need a database, you can <a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/iss/web/infrastructure/databases/">apply for a MySQL account</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          We aim to provide as much information as possible via the pages at <a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/iss/web/">http://www.ncl.ac.uk/iss/web/</a>,
          if you can't find what you're looking for, then you can <a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/iss/search/">search the ISS site</a>. If you're still
          struggling, you can email <a href="mailto:webmaster@ncl.ac.uk">webmaster@ncl.ac.uk</a> and we'll try our best to help.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page is currently appearing as your default homepage. When you upload a file named index.html, this will become your default in it's place.
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>ISS Web Team</em>
        </p>
